<<<code>>>: int location = Yoghurts.getHashMap().entrySet().iterator().next().getKey();
<<<explanation>>>: The method `next()` of the `Iterator` interface returns the next element in the iteration. In the case of a `LinkedHashMap`, the `entrySet()` method returns a set view of the mappings contained in the map. By calling `iterator()` on the set, you can obtain an iterator over the entries. Finally, by calling `next().getKey()`, you can retrieve the key of the first entry in the map.
